title: For Sale:  Three bags (150) 182gr Nosler eTip Bullets
postcontent: Up for grabs I have three bags (150 total bullets) of 182gr (182 grain) Nosler eTip solid copper alloy expanding bullets. These are sold as blems (because they are a run of 182 grain vs 180 gr) but are one of the BEST most premium bullets on the market today--especially for hunters needing a no-lead bullet.  Nosler eTips shoot with every bit the performance of Barnes and then some, and because they are copper alloy, vice pure copper, do not foul your barrel nearly as quickly or badly.  Nosler eTips feature some of if not THE HIGHEST ballistic coefficients of any bullet in their weight--far surpassing the BCs of other bullets like the Ballistic Tip or AMax. Check the specs on the 180s to see what I mean.  For you, that means a much longer-for-weight bullet than anything else out there, combined with superior ballistics, the flattest shooting trajectories, and some of the best long-range terminal performance of anything on the market. Midway and others sell the 180gr eTips for $45-50 per 50.  Here you get three bags for less than the price of two!  With 150 bullets, you can work up your load, sight in the rifle, and STILL have 100 rounds for your elk, moose, whitetail, mulie, black or brown bear hunt or whatever you are after with your 308, 30-06, 300 Win Mag, 300 H&H, or other favorite 308 caliber rifle. Expands reliably down to 1800fps, so with its high BC you should get a little more distance than normal.  If you love the bullet, reloading the 180s vs the 182s shouldn't be much different once you run out.Use Barnes data as a guide if there's no eTip load data on the Nosler site, but start a little lower than normal and work up, looking for pressure signs (all the standard disclaimers).  Buy now and be reloading tomorrow!Looking to sell for $70 face to face (cash only). Rough grip texturing on the Gen4's polymer frame provides a sure hold on the pistol when hands are wet or sweaty, and the enlarged magazine catch is reversible, accommodating left- or right-handed shooters. An integral accessory rail in front of the trigger guard allows for the attachment of a plethora of aftermarket tactical flashlights or laser sights. The dovetailed rear sight is drift adjustable and has a white outline around its notch; the fixed front blade has a white dot. Sight acquisition is quick in any light. The GLOCK 19 Gen4 Semi-Auto Pistol is an ultra-reliable handgun that is easy to learn how to operate and maintain, making it an ideal choice for self-defense, whether it be for concealed carry or at home. The model 19 Gen4 comes with three standard 15-round magazines magazines that comply with various city or state restrictions on magazine capacity.
